The paper deals with the problem of approximating the longest palindrome in a text in the streaming model, which involves algorithms and data structures for processing data in a sequential manner. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the space complexity of algorithms, which is a common theme in cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves combinatorial and graph-theoretic arguments, which are relevant to cs.CGT (Combinatorics and Graph Theory) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
